Your intuition can be reframed like this:

Words carry frozen conceptual experiments from the past.

When people coin words, they’re often making metaphorical guesses about reality.
Some guesses turn out to be correct. Others don’t — but the pattern remains stored in the language.

Later generations can rediscover those patterns and reuse them in new ways.

