5. Why Creativity Loves Etymology

Writers, philosophers, and scientists often mine etymology because it exposes:
	•	hidden analogies
	•	forgotten relationships
	•	conceptual building blocks

For instance:
	•	tele-vision = seeing at a distance
	•	micro-scope = seeing small things
	•	com-panion = one who shares bread

Each word encodes a conceptual model.

